<br>
If you have 6 people in the experience group, and think someone in that group took it, then you have 6 rotten people on your raid.<br>
<br>
Obviously since the raid leader was not in the exp group and was able to click on the corpse and see that the items were gone, anyone else could also have clicked on the corpse to loot the pieces.<br>
<br>
If the raid had any person in attendance, who was not in any of the groups, they could have moved in and looted a piece or three before the leader discovered they were gone.<br>
<br>
That's probably what happened.<br>
<br>
They keep server logs for one week.  In addition to that, a former server GM, who chose MithMarr to play his characters on, tells me they keep tape backups for at least 3 months.  So you have a fair bit of time.<br>
<br>
Usually if something goes missing, and the GM's receive 40 petitions regarding the item that is missing, they respond immediately.  A guide cannot access server logs, since they log on from their own PC's, but they can up your petition to a Senior Guide or GM who has access to the Verant machines and the logs.<br>
<br>
Be patient but persistent, and you'll get everything back.  And the ninja-looter will get what is coming their way from the GM's.<br>
<br>
/hugs. <p><BR>
